Crucially, none of the provided papers (1–5) address NPSS calibration, permutation-based multiple testing correction, or finite-sample concentration over group actions. Papers 2, 3, and 5 discuss calibration in machine learning contexts (LLMs, reading systems, trajectory prediction), but focus on post-hoc confidence recalibration using temperature scaling or regularizers—not significance threshold derivation under non-parametric designs. Paper 1 discusses submodular optimization and has no relevance to statistical calibration. Thus, both ideas are largely free from direct overlap.

